text: Kim Mun-sik (Kim Moon-shik, born 1 December 1928) was a South Korean equestrian. He competed in two events at the 1964 Summer Olympics. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1928 births Category:Possibly living people Category:South Korean male equestrians Category:Olympic equestrians of South Korea Category:Equestrians at the 1964 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
